<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>. . . we cannot decide whether it is an exploit or not because we do not know Sony's true intentions . . .<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I would say we need to apply a &quot;reasonable person&quot; test. Quite simply, would a reasonable person say that the action in question has a detrimental effect on the integrity and/or balance of the game. Furthermore, (and here's where it gets into matter of opinion) is it a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>significant</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> detrimental effect. If so, then it is most likely an exploit.<br>
<br>
In the case of the grouping for buffs example, I think it is most likely an exploit, since Sony has explicitly written code prohibiting the buff from landing on a player of insufficient level. Very high level buffs on low level players have a significant detrimental effect on the balance of PC/mob interaction at the player's level, trivializing content and allowing the PC to chew through the content at a pace far higher than SOE originally intended for a player of that level.<br>
<br>
By the same reasoning, twinking could be considered close to an exploit - high level equipment on low level characters drastically alters PvE balance. SOE has begun to address this with recommended/required levels for new items, although I don't think they have the time nor patience to go through the entire item database and set required/recommended levels for old items.<br>
<br>
In any case, I think trying to come up with a simple, working definition of &quot;exploit&quot; in EQ is about as easy as coming up with a simple, working definition of &quot;wrong&quot; (in the moral sense) in RL. In life, we only really find out if our definition was correct when we die. In EQ, we find out on patch day.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kabach>Kabach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/03 12:36:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25564.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Define &quot;exploit&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
