<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum4/HTML/039635.html">boards.station.sony.com/u...39635.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
KEI being cast on lower levels is not intended, is a workaround done using a bug (group bug), so it is indeed an exploit. It is a rather small exploit, but that's what it is. Just because some noobs on the thread are trying to pass it as right simply because they don't want to lose KEI, or have 'ubers' telling them what to do, or that it's ok since it hasn't been fixed yet, still doesn't change that fact that it's an exploit.<br>
<br>
There is stuff which is iffy though. Is multiquesting an exploit? It is, as it is using flaws into the questing system. SOE does not reimburse items lost on a multiquest for example. Although almost everyone has done MQ one time or another.<br>
<br>
What about ghetto CoH? CoH'ing is not intended in the zone, yet ghetto CoH is not an exploit as really you are playing within the mechanics of the game, not exploiting a bug, and it's also a lot more work then it would be if CoH was done. So while SOE might not like it, It is not an exploit.<br>
<br>
Is quad kiting an exploit? It was never intended by Verant for wizards and druids to kite and kill 4 mobs at a time. Kiting in itself was never intended. But both classes have AE spells. One person found a use for the spells and it has grown. It is not an exploit, although SOE could very well decide that they no longer want it in game and change it around (see AE groups for a good example of a non-exploit change).<br>
<br>
You gotta look at it on a case by case basis, and see wether bugs are in play or not.<br>
<br>
Turonyen<br>
level 65 Enchanter<br>
